               <msContents>
                  <summary>Minhāj al-vuṣūl ilá ʿilm al-ʾuṣūl is the title of one of the works written by Qāz̤ī Bayz̤āvī on the principles of Islamic jurisprudence and presented in the form of an introduction and seven books. Many commentaries have been written on this work, including 'Sirāj-i Vahhāj' by Aḥmad bin Ḥasan Jārbardī (746 Qamarī) and 'Nahāyat al-Sūl fī Sharḥ Minhāj al-vuṣūl' by Asnavī. There is allegedly another commentary on this work called 'al-Ḥanafīyah lil-minhāj ʿalá ḥal al-matn', whose author was not known based on the avaialble sources. The present copy is a summary of the aforementioned commentary, whose author has remained unknown too.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_742-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">Principles of Islamic jurisprudence</note>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3032">Ikhtiṣār al-ḥanafīyah lil-minhāj ʿalá ḥal al-matn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_3032">اختصار الحنفیه للمنهاج علی حل المتن</title>
                     <author key="person_f4278">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Unknown.</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">بسمله، حمدله، و بعد… من لم یظن فی قوله الا محض الخیر الی اختصار الشرح المسمی بالحنفیه للمنهاج علی حل المتن و نصرة المذهب وشیی من الاسوله…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true">… لا ینسخ سیی من الادلة و لا ینسخ من الادلة به ایضا اما النص والاجماع ای لانها…</explicit>
